POLICE have named a driver who died when his van left the road.
James Whyte, 47, from Peebles in the Borders, died when his black Vauxhall Vivaro van came off the road on the B6363 Lauder to Stow road at around 7.30pm last night.
Police Sergeant Ross Drummond said: &quot;Sadly the driver died at the scene and road policing officers are now carrying out enquiries to establish the circumstances.
&quot;We are appealing for any witnesses to this collision, or who saw the black Vauxhall Vivaro van travelling from Stow to Lauder, to contact Police Scotland on 101.&quot;
